00\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-with-espresso-glaze/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Pumpkin Scones with Espresso Glaze.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-scaled.jpg 1636w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-728x979.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-768x1033.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-1142x1536.jpg 1142w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-1523x2048.jpg 1523w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-150x202.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1636px) 100vw, 1636px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201636%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-scaled.jpg 1636w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-728x979.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-768x1033.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-1142x1536.jpg 1142w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-1523x2048.jpg 1523w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-150x202.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-3-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eOne of the reasons I love these so much is because they take barely any time at all. Once the ingredients are combined, you pat the dough into circles, cut it into triangles and bake for 15ish minutes or less. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThey are easy, fast and make a nice batch that lasts for the week! Or that you can share with friends. Or that you can freeze for later. Priorities! \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"pumpkin scones with espresso glaze\" width=\"1752\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-with-espresso-glaze/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Pumpkin Scones with Espresso Glaze.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-scaled.jpg 1752w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-728x914.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-768x965.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-1223x1536.jpg 1223w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-1631x2048.jpg 1631w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-150x188.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1752px) 100vw, 1752px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201752%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/pumpkin-scones-espresso-glaze-4-scaled.jpg 1752w, https://www.howsweeteats.co